9 Principles
************

   • No customization options that affect the style of individual
     components (e.g.  change the color of the mode line, remove bold,
     etc.)!  Either you like them or you don’t.  To change faces, it is
     better to do it in user-level configurations (report the issue and
     we can help with the relevant code).  Providing customizations that
     refashion a wide set of themes is not maintainable.

   • Curated list of supported packages.  I will only cover what I use
     and/or know is in a well-maintained state.  Styling a package
     requires a lot of work as one must (i) know how the package works,
     (ii) see all its interfaces in action, (iii) make sure that the
     color combinations look consistent with the rest of the theme.

   • Minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 against the main background (WCAG
     AA standard).  Use my ‘modus-themes’ package (also built into Emacs
     28 or higher) if you need top-class accessibility.


